CreateActCtxW.description: The CreateActCtx function creates an activation context.

EncryptMessage.description: The EncryptMessage (General) function encrypts a message to provide privacy. EncryptMessage (General) allows an application to choose among cryptographic algorithms supported by the chosen mechanism. The EncryptMessage (General) function uses the security context referenced by the context handle. Some packages do not have messages to be encrypted or decrypted but rather provide an integrity hash that can be checked.

GetSystemMetrics.description: Retrieves the specified     system metric or system configuration setting.

WriteConsoleA.description: Writes a character string to a console screen buffer beginning at the current cursor location.

CertControlStore.description: The CertControlStore function allows an application to be notified when there is a difference between the contents of a cached store in use and the contents of that store as it is persisted to storage. Differences can occur as another process makes a change that affects the store as it is persisted.

CertOpenStore.description: The CertOpenStore function opens a certificate store by using a specified store provider type. While this function can open a certificate store for most purposes, CertOpenSystemStore is recommended to open the most common certificate stores. CertOpenStore is required for more complex options and special cases.

CryptAcquireContextA.description: The CryptAcquireContext function is used to acquire a handle to a particular key container within a particular cryptographic service provider (CSP). This returned handle is used in calls to CryptoAPI functions that use the selected CSP.

CryptCreateHash.description: The CryptCreateHash function initiates the hashing of a stream of data. It creates and returns to the calling application a handle to a cryptographic service provider (CSP) hash object. This handle is used in subsequent calls to CryptHashData and CryptHashSessionKey to hash session keys and other streams of data.

CryptDecodeObjectEx.description: The CryptDecodeObjectEx function decodes a structure of the type indicated by the lpszStructType parameter. CryptDecodeObjectEx offers a significant performance improvement over CryptDecodeObject by supporting memory allocation with the CRYPT_DECODE_ALLOC_FLAG value.

CryptHashData.description: The CryptHashData function adds data to a specified hash object. This function and CryptHashSessionKey can be called multiple times to compute the hash of long or discontinuous data streams.

IsDebuggerPresent.description: Determines whether the calling process is being debugged by a user-mode debugger.

MessageBoxTimeoutA.description: Determines whether the calling process is being debugged by a user-mode debugger.

NtEnumerateKey.description: The ZwEnumerateKey routine returns information about a subkey of an open registry key. NtEnumerateKey and ZwEnumerateKey are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtEnumerateKey routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwEnumerateKey routine. For more information, see ZwEnumerateKey.

NtEnumerateValueKey.description: The ZwEnumerateKey routine returns information about a subkey of an open registry key. NtEnumerateValueKey and ZwEnumerateValueKey are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtEnumerateValueKey routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwEnumerateValueKey routine. For more information, see ZwEnumerateValueKey.

NtFreeVirtualMemory.description: The ZwFreeVirtualMemory routine releases, decommits, or both, a region of pages within the virtual address space of a specified process.

NtOpenKey.description: The ZwOpenKey routine opens an existing registry key. NtOpenKey and ZwOpenKey are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtOpenKey routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwOpenKey routine. For more information, see ZwOpenKey.

NtOpenSection.description: The ZwOpenSection routine opens a handle for an existing section object. NtOpenSection and ZwOpenSection are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtOpenSection routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwOpenSection routine. For more information, see ZwOpenSection

NtQueryValueKey.description: The ZwQueryValueKey routine returns a value entry for a registry key. NtQueryValueKey and ZwQueryValueKey are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtQueryValueKey routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwQueryValueKey routine. For more information, see ZwQueryValueKey.

NtSetValueKey.description: The ZwSetValueKey routine creates or replaces a registry key's value entry. NtSetValueKey and ZwSetValueKey are two versions of the same Windows Native System Services routine. The NtSetValueKey routine in the Windows kernel is not directly accessible to kernel-mode drivers. However, kernel-mode drivers can access this routine indirectly by calling the ZwSetValueKey routine. For more information, see ZwSetValueKey.

LdrGetDllHandle.description: Retrieves a module handle for the specified module. The module must have been loaded by the calling process.

CopyFileA.description: Copies an existing file to a new file.

FindFirstFileExW.description: Searches a directory for a file or subdirectory with a name and attributes that match those     specified.

GetFileAttributesW.description: Retrieves file system attributes for a specified file or directory.

GetFileSize.description: Retrieves the size of the specified file, in bytes.

GetFileSizeEx.description: Retrieves the size of the specified file.

GetFileType.description: Retrieves the file type of the specified file.

GetShortPathNameW.description: Retrieves the short path form of the specified path.

GetTempPathW.description: Retrieves the path of the directory designated for temporary files.

NtCreateFile.description: Creates or opens a file or I/O device. The most commonly used I/O devices are as follows: file, file     stream, directory, physical disk, volume, console buffer, tape drive, communications resource, mailslot, and     pipe. The function returns a handle that can be used to access the file or device for various types of     I/O depending on the file or device and the flags and attributes specified.

NtMapViewOfSection.description: Moves the file pointer of the specified file.

NtOpenDirectoryObject.description: Sets the physical file size for the specified file to the current position of the file pointer.

NtOpenFile.description: Creates, opens, reopens, or deletes a file.

NtReadFile.description: Reads data from the specified file or input/output (I/O) device. Reads occur at the position specified     by the file pointer if supported by the device.

NtWriteFile.description: Writes data to the specified file or input/output (I/O) device.

SetFilePointer.description: Moves the file pointer of the specified file.

NtSetInformationFile.description: The following functions are used to manage files.

DrawTextExW.description: The DrawTextEx function draws formatted text in the specified rectangle.

CoCreateInstance.description: Creates a single uninitialized object of the class associated with a specified CLSID.

CoInitializeEx.description: Initializes the COM library for use by the calling thread, sets the thread's concurrency model, and creates a new apartment for the thread if one is required.

CoUninitialize.description: Closes the COM library on the current thread, unloads all DLLs loaded by the thread, frees any other resources that the thread maintains, and forces all RPC connections on the thread to close.

NtDeviceIoControlFile.description: The HttpCreateUrlGroup function creates a URL Group  under the specified  server session.

LdrGetProcedureAddress.description: Gets the procedure address of the specified function in the signed library.

GetAdaptersAddresses.description: The GetAdaptersAddresses function retrieves the addresses associated with the adapters on the local computer.

GetBestInterfaceEx.description: The GetBestInterfaceEx function retrieves the index of the interface that has the best route to the specified IPv4 or IPv6 address.

GlobalMemoryStatusEx.description: Retrieves information about the system's current usage of both physical and virtual memory.

NtAllocateVirtualMemory.description: Reserves, commits, or changes the state  of a region of memory within the virtual address space of the specified process, and     specifies the NUMA node for the physical memory.

NtCreateSection.description: Creates or opens a named or unnamed file mapping object for a specified file.

NtProtectVirtualMemory.description: Provides an efficient mechanism to bring into memory potentially discontiguous virtual address ranges     in a process address space.

CreateProcessInternalW.description: Creates a new process and its primary thread. The new process runs in the security context of the user represented by the specified token.

CreateThread.description: Creates a thread to execute within the virtual address space of the calling process.

NtCreateThreadEx.description: Creates a thread to execute within the virtual address space of the calling process.

NtDelayExecution.description: Suspends the current thread until the specified condition is met. Execution resumes when one of the following occurs:

NtOpenProcess.description: Opens an existing local process object.

NtQueryInformationFile.description: [NtQueryInformationProcess may be altered or unavailable in future versions of Windows. Applications should use the alternate functions listed in this topic.]

NtResumeThread.description: Decrements a thread's suspend count. When the suspend count is decremented to zero, the execution of the thread is resumed.

NtTerminateProcess.description: Terminates the specified process and all of its threads.

NtCreateKey.description: Enumerates the values for the specified open registry key. The function copies one indexed value name and data block for the key each time it is called.

NtOpenKeyEx.description: Opens the specified registry key. Note that key names are not case sensitive.

NtQueryKey.description: Retrieves the type and data for the specified value name associated with an open registry key.

RegCloseKey.description: Closes a handle to the specified registry key.

RegCreateKeyExW.description: Creates the specified registry key. If the key already exists, the function opens it. Note that key names are not case sensitive.

RegDeleteValueW.description: Removes a named value from the specified registry key. Note that value names are not case sensitive.

RegEnumKeyExA.description: Enumerates the subkeys of the specified open registry key. The function retrieves information about one subkey each time it is called.

RegEnumKeyExW.description: Enumerates the subkeys of the specified open registry key. The function retrieves information about one subkey each time it is called.

RegEnumValueW.description: Enumerates the values for the specified open registry key. The function copies one indexed value name and data block for the key each time it is called.

RegOpenKeyExA.description: Opens the specified registry key. Note that key names are not case sensitive.

RegOpenKeyExW.description: Opens the specified registry key. Note that key names are not case sensitive.

RegQueryInfoKeyW.description: Retrieves information about the specified registry key.

RegQueryValueExA.description: Retrieves the type and data for the specified value name associated with an open registry key.

RegQueryValueExW.description: Retrieves the type and data for the specified value name associated with an open registry key.

RegSetValueExA.description: Sets the data and type of a specified value under a registry key.

RegSetValueExW.description: Sets the data and type of a specified value under a registry key.

FindResourceA.description: Determines the location of a resource with the specified type and name in the specified module.

FindResourceExW.description: Determines the location of the resource with the specified type, name, and language in the specified module.

LoadResource.description: Retrieves a handle that can be used to obtain a pointer to the first byte of the specified resource in memory.

SizeofResource.description: Retrieves the size, in bytes, of the specified resource.

OpenSCManagerW.description: Establishes a connection to the service control manager on the specified computer and opens the specified service control manager database.

LoadStringA.description: Loads a string resource from the executable file associated with a specified module, copies the string into a buffer, and appends a terminating null character.

LoadStringW.description: Loads a string resource from the executable file associated with a specified module, copies the string into a buffer, and appends a terminating null character.

SetUnhandledExceptionFilter.description: Enables an application to supersede the top-level exception handler of each thread of a process.

HttpQueryInfoA.description: Creates or opens a named or unnamed event object.

NtCreateMutant.description: Creates or opens a named or unnamed event object.

NtOpenMutant.description: Opens an existing named mutex object.

GetComputerNameA.description: Retrieves the NetBIOS name of the local computer. This name is established at system startup, when the system reads it from the registry.

GetNativeSystemInfo.description: Retrieves information about the current system to an application running under WOW64. If the function is called from a 64-bit application, it is equivalent to the GetSystemInfo function.

GetSystemDirectoryA.description: Retrieves the path of the system directory. The system directory contains system files such as dynamic-link libraries and drivers.

GetSystemDirectoryW.description: Retrieves the path of the system directory. The system directory contains system files such as dynamic-link libraries and drivers.

GetSystemInfo.description: Retrieves information about the current system.

GetSystemWindowsDirectoryW.description: Retrieves the path of the shared Windows directory on a multi-user system.

GetUserNameA.description: Retrieves the name of the user associated with the current thread.

GetUserNameExW.description: Retrieves the name of the user or other security principal associated with the calling thread. You can specify the format of the returned name.

NtQuerySystemInformation.description: [NtQuerySystemInformation may be altered or unavailable in future versions of Windows. Applications should use the alternate functions listed in this topic.]

RtlDecompressBuffer.description: [NtQuerySystemInformation may be altered or unavailable in future versions of Windows. Applications should use the alternate functions listed in this topic.]

GetSystemTimeAsFileTime.description: Retrieves the current system date and time. The information is in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) format.

SetFileTime.description: Sets the date and time that the specified file or directory was created, last accessed, or last     modified.

CreateToolhelp32Snapshot.description: Takes a snapshot of the specified processes, as well as the heaps, modules, and threads used by these processes.

Module32FirstW.description: Retrieves information about the first module associated with a process.

Module32NextW.description: Retrieves information about the next module associated with a process or thread.

Process32FirstW.description: Retrieves information about the first process encountered in a system snapshot.

Process32NextW.description: Retrieves information about the next process recorded in a system snapshot.

Thread32First.description: Retrieves information about the first thread of any process encountered in a system snapshot.

Thread32Next.description: Retrieves information about the next thread of any process encountered in the system memory snapshot.

LdrLoadDll.description: The following example uses the CreateFileMapping function with the SEC_LARGE_PAGES flag to use large pages. It requires Windows Server 2003 with Service Pack 1 (SP1) or later.

SetEndOfFile.description: The following example uses the CreateFileMapping function with the SEC_LARGE_PAGES flag to use large pages. It requires Windows Server 2003 with Service Pack 1 (SP1) or later.

InternetConnectA.description: Opens an File Transfer Protocol (FTP) or HTTP session for a given site.

InternetCrackUrlW.description: Cracks a URL into its component parts.

InternetOpenA.description: Initializes an application's use of the WinINet functions.

InternetOpenUrlA.description: Opens a resource specified by a complete FTP or HTTP URL.

InternetQueryOptionA.description: Queries an Internet option on the specified handle.

InternetReadFile.description: Reads data from a handle opened by the InternetOpenUrl, FtpOpenFile, or HttpOpenRequest function.

NtUnmapViewOfSection.description: TheWNetAddConnection2 function makes a connection to a network resource and can redirect a local device to the network resource.

GetAddrInfoW.description: The GetAddrInfoW function provides protocol-independent translation from a Unicode host name to an address.

NtQueryAttributesFile.description: The GetAddrInfoW function provides protocol-independent translation from a Unicode host name to an address.

WSARecv.description: The WSARecv function receives data from a connected socket or a bound connectionless socket.

WSASend.description: The WSASend function sends data on a connected socket.

WSASocketA.description: The WSASocket function creates a socket that is bound to a specific transport-service provider.

WSASocketW.description: The WSASocket function creates a socket that is bound to a specific transport-service provider.

WSAStartup.description: The WSAStartup function initiates use of the Winsock DLL by a process.

bind.description: The bind function associates a local address with a socket.

closesocket.description: The closesocket function closes an existing socket.

connect.description: The connect function establishes a connection to a specified socket.

gethostbyname.description: The gethostbyname function retrieves host information corresponding to a host name from a host database.

getsockname.description: The getsockname function retrieves the local name for a socket.

ioctlsocket.description: The ioctlsocket function controls the I/O mode of a socket.

recv.description: The recv function receives data from a connected socket or a bound connectionless socket.

send.description: The send function sends data on a connected socket.

setsockopt.description: The setsockopt function sets a socket option.

shutdown.description: The shutdown function disables sends or receives on a socket.

socket.description: The socket function creates a socket that is bound to a specific transport service provider.
